"{{padlr|Tlpl}}" {{big|⇒}} "{{padlr|'''T'''}}emplate {{padlr|'''l'''}}ink, {{padlr|'''pl'''}}ain"

Produces a "plain" link{{aside|i.e. a link without "Template:" prefix, braces, etc}}to the template named by the first parameter. If a second parameter is also supplied, it is used as the text for the link.

===Syntax and examples===
: {{tlx|tlpl|''template_name''}}
: {{tlx|tlpl|''template_name''|''link_text''}}

: {{tnfpad|tlpl|Example}} produces: {{tlpl|Example}}
: {{tnfpad|tlpl|Example|the "Example" template}} produces: {{tlpl|Example|the "Example" template}}

===See also===
* {{tlpad|c}}, the same kind of template for a category.
* {{tlpad|tl}} and {{tlpad|tnf}}, similar templates that include, respectively, braces as well as a link and braces without a link.
* {{cl|Internal template-link templates}} for more templates providing template links within Wikipedia.

