"{{padlr|tlbare}}" {{big|⇒}} "{{padlr|'''t'''}}emplate {{padlr|'''l'''}}ink, {{padlr|'''b'''}}are"

A template in the same vein as the category-linking template {{tlpad|c}}, producing a "bare" link{{aside|i.e. without "Template:" prefix, braces, etc}}to the template named by the first parameter. If a second parameter is supplied, it is used in place of the first as the link's text.

===Syntax and examples===
: {{tlx|tlbare|''template_name''}}
: {{tlx|tlbare|''template_name''|''link_text''}}

: {{tlcplain|tlbare|Example}} produces: {{tlbare|Example}}
: {{tlcplain|tlbare|Example|the "Example" template}} produces: {{tlbare|Example|the "Example" template}}

===See also===
* {{tlpad|c}}, the same kind of template for a category.
* {{tlpad|tl}} and {{tlpad|tnf}}, similar templates that include, respectively, braces as well as a link; and braces without a link.
* {{cl|Internal template-link templates}} for more templates providing template links within Wikipedia.

