"{{padlr|tlbare}}" {{big|⇒}} "{{padlr|{{bigger|'''t'''}}}}emplate {{padlr|{{bigger|'''l'''}}}}ink, '''bare'''"

A template in the same vein as the category-linking template {{tlpad|c}}, producing a "bare" link{{aside|i.e. without "Template:" prefix, braces, etc}}to the template named by the first parameter. If a second parameter is supplied, it is used in place of the first as the link's text.

===Syntax===
: {{tlx|tlbare|''template_name''}}
: {{tlx|tlbare|''template_name''|''link_text''}}

===Examples===
: {{tcpl|tlbare|Example}} produces: {{tlbare|Example}}
: {{tcpl|tlbare|Example|the "Example" template}} produces: {{tlbare|Example|the "Example" template}}

===Resizing===
: {{tlx|tlbare|''N''%|''template_name''}}
: {{tlx|tlbare|''N''%|''template_name''|''link_text''}}
If the first parameter ends in a percent sign ("%"), it will be treated as a font-size setting for the template's output. For example:
{{Aligned table
 |cols=3 |col2style=padding-right:0.65em;
 | {{tcpl|tlbare|Example}}     | produces: | {{tlbare|Example}}
 | {{tcpl|tlbare|90%|Example}} | produces: | {{tlbare|90%|Example}}
 | {{tcpl|tlbare|90|Example}}  | produces: | {{tlbare|90|Example}}
}}

===See also===
* {{tlpad|c}}, the same kind of template for a category.
* {{tlpad|tl}} and {{tpad|tnf}}, similar templates that include, respectively, braces as well as a link; and braces without a link.
* {{cl|Internal template-link templates}} for more templates providing template links within Wikipedia.

